Shona Banda, 37, is fighting for custody of her 11-year-old son after his comments about marijuana at a school presentation prompted police to search her home . 
  Banda wrote a book about how she uses cannabis oil to treat her Crohn's disease . 
  Her son was taken from her custody on March 24 after school officials reported his comments to child protection services . 
  Police searched her home without a warrant and found marijuana in plant and oil . 
  She has a custody hearing Monday in Garden City, Kansas . 
 